And the big French hacks have been revealed
In the Copenhagen Agreement, developed countries committed to making $30 billion in 2010-2012.
The European Union has promised €7.2 billion for three years and France €1.26 billion (that is €420 million a year).
At the start of COP16, the EU pulled out a large ace to convince its partners about the reality of its commitment to financing fast start: a report detailing the actions of its Member States, a press conference, a grand side event, the distribution of brochures...
