In particular, France's overall support for developing countries may remain unchanged (or even reduced) to comply with its commitment to financing of new and additional...
Another crucial element is the distribution of gifts and loans.
There is no rule yet, and everyone chooses their own way of calculating.
Some, such as France, consider that 1€ borrowed is equal to 1€ donated.
Obviously, this is hard to prove: the effort is not comparable.
If the use of loans can be documented for some investments that are profitable (often related to emission reduction projects, consisting in more efficient technologies), it is foolish to present one euro that we will receive, as equivalent to one euro we give... . . . we should not understand it from the title of our commitments, but as the price of a loan for a creditor country (i.e. the equivalent of interest rate).
